The full FFmpeg source code can be downloaded from the ffmpeg project's web page at 
http://ffmpeg.sourceforge.net/index.php

MHKKit is distributed with a universal binary version of libavutil and libavcodec, a subset of
the functional libraries of FFmpeg. At the time of writing, the FFmpeg project does not support 
"universal binary compiling". My current process is to compile on a PowerPC Mac, compile 
on an Intel Mac and create the universal binary using lipo. I am currently using Mac OS X 10.5 for 
compiling, which due to a bug in the new ld forces mmx to be disabled on Intel.

FFmpeg was compiled with the following options:

./configure --prefix=$HOME/ffmpeg --disable-static --enable-shared --enable-pthreads --disable-ffmpeg --disable-ffserver --disable-ffplay --disable-encoders --disable-decoders --disable-muxers --disable-demuxers --disable-parsers --disable-protocols --disable-devices --enable-decoder=mp2 --enable-demuxer=mp3 --enable-parser=mpegaudio --enable-protocol=file --disable-strip --disable-debug --extra-cflags="-mmacosx-version-min=10.4 -gdwarf-2" --extra-ldflags="-mmacosx-version-min=10.4" --disable-mmx

The dsymutil tool was used to generate the dSYM file. strip -x was then applied to the dylib files.
